      <title>How to make AJAX calls in Rails 5.1 with or without jQuery</title>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;figure data-trix-attachment="{&amp;quot;contentType&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;image&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;height&amp;quot;:1538,&amp;quot;url&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2017-08-23/1503487325411-ajax.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;width&amp;quot;:2690}" data-trix-content-type="image" class="attachment attachment--preview"&gt;&lt;img src="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2017-08-23/1503487325411-ajax.png" width="2690" height="1538"&gt;&lt;figcaption class="attachment__caption"&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Rails shipped without jQuery as a dependency for the first time with version 5.1. Rails used to rely on jQuery for &lt;a href="http://guides.rubyonrails.org/working_with_javascript_in_rails.html#unobtrusive-javascript"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unobtrusive JavaScript&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; features but now ships with its own library &lt;a href="https://github.com/rails/rails/tree/master/actionview/app/assets/javascripts"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;rails-ujs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; with the same features.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;One of the most common use cases for jQuery in Rails was making AJAX calls through forms and links. If you’re using Rails 5.1 for the first time, you might get confused about how to make AJAX calls, especially things like data formats and including CSRF tokens.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;So this little tutorial walks you through a few ways you can do so.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If you're using a standard Rails form or link for AJAX calls, Rails still offers some great in-built methods. However, when you're not using those methods, for example when you're &lt;a href="https://learnetto.com/users/hrishio/courses/react-rails-course"&gt;building a React UI for a Rails app&lt;/a&gt;, then you will find this tutorial helpful.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. Use rails-ujs (no jQuery)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;A new Rails 5.1 app automatically includes the rails-ujs script in the app’s application.js file:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;//= require rails-ujs&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div&gt;If you don’t want to include it there and use it only selectively, say if you’re making a separate React frontend with Rails’s new webpacker support, then you can do use rails-ujs by installing it as a package:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;$ yarn add rails-ujs&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div&gt;And then import and start it in your JavaScript file:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;import Rails from 'rails-ujs'
Rails.start()&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div&gt;Remove this line from application.js :&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;//= require rails-ujs&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div&gt;Now let’s say we want to make an AJAX POST call to an API endpoint/things with some data which looks like this:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;mydata = {
 thing: {
  field1: value1,
  field2: value2,
}}&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div&gt;Making an AJAX POST call with rails-ujs looks identical to making it with jQuery:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;Rails.ajax({
  type: "POST", 
  url: "/things",
  data: mydata,
  success: function(repsonse){...},
  error: function(repsonse){...}
})&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div&gt;Except for one thing! As far as I can tell, you can’t simply send JSON data. So we need to convert mydata to application/x-www-form-urlencoded content type manually like this:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;mydata = 'thing[field1]=value1&amp;amp;thing[field2]=value2'&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div&gt;jQuery does this conversion automatically before submitting a request.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I assumed rails-ujs has some automatic way of doing it, but I couldn’t find anything in the docs or &lt;a href="https://github.com/rails/rails/blob/master/actionview/app/assets/javascripts/rails-ujs/utils/ajax.coffee"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;code&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If you know, &lt;a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/45820587/how-do-you-send-json-data-in-a-rails-ujs-rails-ajax-post-call-not-using-jquery"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;let me know&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;rails-ujs automatically takes care of including the CSRF token with the request.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2. Use jQuery&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If the manual data conversion puts you off, you can still use jQuery. You may be relying on jQuery for other things in your app anyway, so here are couple of ways of using jQuery with Rails for making AJAX calls:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2.1 Use the jquery-rails gem&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;This gem used to be automatically included in previous versions of Rails. You can install it by adding it to your Gemfile:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;gem 'jquery-rails'&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div&gt;Then run:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;$ bundle install&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div&gt;And include jquery and jquery_ujs in your application.js file:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;//= require jquery
//= require jquery_ujs&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div&gt;That’s all you need. Now you can make your AJAX call in the usual way:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;$.ajax({
  type: "POST", 
  url: "/things",
  data: mydata,
  success: function(data, textStatus, jqXHR){...},
  error: function(jqXHR, textStatus, errorThrown){...}
})&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div&gt;jquery_ujs takes care of including the CSRF token and jquery converts the data to application/x-www-form-urlencoded content type automatically.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2.2. Use jquery package from npm&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If you don’t want to use a gemified version of jQuery, you can install it as a JavaScript package from npm:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;$ yarn add jquery
$ yarn add jquery-ujs&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div&gt;Then import them in your JavaScript file:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;import $ from ‘jquery’
import {} from ‘jquery-ujs’&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div&gt;Make sure to remove the jquery-rails gem if you have it installed and remove jquery and jquery_ujs from application.js.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;You may get an error saying jQuery is not defined. In your webpack config file add this to the config.plugins array:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;new webpack.ProvidePlugin({
 $: “jquery”,
 jQuery: “jquery”
}),&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div&gt;And now you will be able to use jQuery for making your AJAX calls.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3. Use axios&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/mzabriskie/axios"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;axios&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is a promise-based HTTP library. You can use it to make HTTP requests from node.js (on the server) and also AJAX requests from the browser.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;It’s a good alternative if you don’t need any of jQuery’s other features. To use axios in a Rails 5.1 app (with webpacker), install it:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;$ yarn add axios&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div&gt;Then import it in your JavaScript file:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;import axios from ‘axios’&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div&gt;Now we can make the AJAX call like this:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;axios({
  method: 'POST', 
  url: '/things',
  data: mydata,
  headers: {
    'X-CSRF-Token': document.querySelector("meta[name=csrf-token]").content
  }
})
.then(function(response) {...},
.catch(function(error) {...}
})&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div&gt;A few things to note here:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;We have to include the CSRF token header. Unlike jquery_ujs and rails-ujs, it’s not automatically included with axios requests.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;We can specify it as a default setting to avoid repeating it in all our AJAX calls:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;pre&gt;const csrfToken = document.querySelector("meta[name=csrf-token]").content
axios.defaults.headers.common[‘X-CSRF-Token’] = csrfToken&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;div&gt;We can access the success and error responses using the promises syntax &lt;em&gt;.then&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Another option is to use &lt;a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Fetch_API/Using_Fetch"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;fetch&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but it’s an experimental API and not available by default in all browsers. So you’re best off using &lt;a href="https://github.com/github/fetch"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Github’s polyfill library&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. I prefer axios to fetch because fetch responses need to be first converted to json and the error handling can also be confusing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Wed, 23 Aug 2017 10:32:56 +0000</pubDate>
      <link>https://learnetto.com/blog/rails-ajax</link>
      <guid>https://learnetto.com/blog/rails-ajax</guid>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>How to launch your startup on BetaList - 8 lessons from Learnetto</title>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;figure data-trix-attachment="{&amp;quot;contentType&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;image/png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filename&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;img2.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filesize&amp;quot;:183344,&amp;quot;height&amp;quot;:575,&amp;quot;href&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455539993409-img2.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;url&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455539993409-img2.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;width&amp;quot;:529}" data-trix-content-type="image/png" data-trix-attributes="{&amp;quot;caption&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Betalist gave us a nice boost of signups to our beta mailing list&amp;quot;}" class="attachment attachment--preview attachment--png"&gt;&lt;a href="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455539993409-img2.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455539993409-img2.png" width="529" height="575"&gt;&lt;figcaption class="attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited"&gt;Betalist gave us a nice boost of signups to our beta mailing list&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="http://learnetto.com/"&gt;Learnetto&lt;/a&gt; got featured on Betalist last week on Monday 1st Feb 2016 — &lt;a href="https://betalist.com/startups/learnetto"&gt;https://betalist.com/startups/learnetto&lt;/a&gt;. It was a good experience for us and gave a much needed kickstart to our marketing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;figure data-trix-attachment="{&amp;quot;contentType&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;image/png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filename&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;img3.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filesize&amp;quot;:341285,&amp;quot;height&amp;quot;:547,&amp;quot;href&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540040408-img3.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;url&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540040408-img3.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;width&amp;quot;:1150}" data-trix-content-type="image/png" data-trix-attributes="{&amp;quot;caption&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Learnetto listing on Betalist&amp;quot;}" class="attachment attachment--preview attachment--png"&gt;&lt;a href="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540040408-img3.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540040408-img3.png" width="1150" height="547"&gt;&lt;figcaption class="attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited"&gt;Learnetto listing on Betalist&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I just want to quickly share our results and some tips so that you can get the most for your startup if you decide to list on Betalist.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Numbers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;We had just over 50 subscribers before Betalist. I hadn’t started building the email list yet. Betalist was the first serious effort.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;figure data-trix-attachment="{&amp;quot;contentType&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;image/png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filename&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;img4.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filesize&amp;quot;:11544,&amp;quot;height&amp;quot;:89,&amp;quot;href&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540071998-img4.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;url&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540071998-img4.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;width&amp;quot;:273}" data-trix-content-type="image/png" data-trix-attributes="{&amp;quot;caption&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Our mailing list numbers (as of 10th Feb 2016)&amp;quot;}" class="attachment attachment--preview attachment--png"&gt;&lt;a href="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540071998-img4.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540071998-img4.png" width="273" height="89"&gt;&lt;figcaption class="attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited"&gt;Our mailing list numbers (as of 10th Feb 2016)&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So far, in the last 10 days our mailing list got around 175 new subscribers, almost all of which came from Betalist. 74 of these new signups came on the first day of listing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;figure data-trix-attachment="{&amp;quot;contentType&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;image/png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filename&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;img1.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filesize&amp;quot;:8102,&amp;quot;height&amp;quot;:278,&amp;quot;href&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540147810-img1.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;url&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540147810-img1.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;width&amp;quot;:800}" data-trix-content-type="image/png" data-trix-attributes="{&amp;quot;caption&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Our mailing list growth&amp;quot;}" class="attachment attachment--preview attachment--png"&gt;&lt;a href="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540147810-img1.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540147810-img1.png" width="800" height="278"&gt;&lt;figcaption class="attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited"&gt;Our mailing list growth&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If I were a cool growth hacker, I’d say we 5x’d our subscriber base, but since we were starting with such a small number, that’d be a ridiculous thing to say.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Having read other people’s experiences, getting 100–200 new subscribers seems a reasonable result to expect, regardless of the starting point.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Traffic&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;As expected, we got a nice spike on the day, getting up to 200 sessions, which then tapered off over the next 3 days and settled on a higher base of 60–70 sessions per day.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;figure data-trix-attachment="{&amp;quot;contentType&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;image/png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filename&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;img5.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filesize&amp;quot;:28300,&amp;quot;height&amp;quot;:296,&amp;quot;href&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540176739-img5.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;url&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540176739-img5.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;width&amp;quot;:919}" data-trix-content-type="image/png" data-trix-attributes="{&amp;quot;caption&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Daily traffic before and after our Betalist feature&amp;quot;}" class="attachment attachment--preview attachment--png"&gt;&lt;a href="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540176739-img5.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540176739-img5.png" width="919" height="296"&gt;&lt;figcaption class="attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited"&gt;Daily traffic before and after our Betalist feature&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;figure data-trix-attachment="{&amp;quot;contentType&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;image/png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filename&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;img6.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filesize&amp;quot;:52718,&amp;quot;height&amp;quot;:357,&amp;quot;href&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540184961-img6.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;url&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540184961-img6.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;width&amp;quot;:400}" data-trix-content-type="image/png" data-trix-attributes="{&amp;quot;caption&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Google Analytics Real Time Dashboard&amp;quot;}" class="attachment attachment--preview attachment--png"&gt;&lt;a href="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540184961-img6.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540184961-img6.png" width="400" height="357"&gt;&lt;figcaption class="attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited"&gt;Google Analytics Real Time Dashboard&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Note that most of this traffic is from Betalist, but not all of it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Was it worth it?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Listing on Betalist is free but because of the sheer volume of submissions they get now, it can take a couple of months before your startup gets listed. I certainly didn’t have that long to wait around, so I paid for the expedited listing — $99 gets you listed within 2–3 days.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;That means so far I’ve spent just over 50 cents to acquire each new subscriber. In other words, each of them will need to spend 35 British pence on Learnetto for us to get a positive ROI.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I’m pretty sure some of the subscribers will buy a course on Learnetto in the coming weeks. Even if a couple of them do, we’ll have made our money back.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;But, besides just the ROI calculation, I think it was worth the effort to get featured on Betalist. I’d been meaning to launch the site’s landing page for a while and when it finally landed on Betalist, things got real. It generated a good amount of buzz and calmed my nerves a bit (&lt;em&gt;What if no one signs up???&lt;/em&gt;). The site also got picked up by a few other directories which is now sending us a steady trickle of traffic.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;One small complaint/misgiving/icky-feeling&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;One strange thing I noticed is that the &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/BetaList/status/694176073253257216"&gt;Betalist tweet about Learnetto&lt;/a&gt; got a lot of retweets from accounts which only seem to do that — tweet Betalist pages.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I checked some of Betalist’s other tweets about other startups and noticed that they all get roughly the same number of retweets — around 140–160.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;My guess is that Betalist hires some of these people, which is ok I guess, if it leads to some more traffic and signups for you. But I’m sharing this so you have a more realistic view of the “buzz”.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;EDIT: Betalist founder Marc just clarified that they don’t hire anyone to do this. See &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://medium.com/@marckohlbrugge/we-don-t-hire-anyone-or-use-any-bots-but-there-are-a-fair-amount-of-people-retweeting-our-startup-d3d94b72f7b7#.i34pkibk5"&gt;&lt;em&gt;his comment here&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; for details.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Anyway, what does all this mean for you?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If you’re on the fence about it, I think you should give it a go. If you’re serious about your project and it’s not just one of your many ideas that you’re not sure about, I also recommend paying and getting featured on a specific date. If you wait around for 2 months just to launch a landing page, you might give up on the idea itself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Here are the top 8 lessons for how you can get the most out of it, based on our experience:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Make a compelling landing page — design and content&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;div&gt;Confession time! 🙊&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I submitted the site originally back in November but &lt;em&gt;got rejected by them&lt;/em&gt;. 😡&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;The reason they gave me was that the design looked too much like a template and wasn’t custom enough.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;figure data-trix-attachment="{&amp;quot;contentType&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;image/png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filename&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;img7.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filesize&amp;quot;:346132,&amp;quot;height&amp;quot;:409,&amp;quot;href&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540276490-img7.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;url&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540276490-img7.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;width&amp;quot;:800}" data-trix-content-type="image/png" data-trix-attributes="{&amp;quot;caption&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;The old landing page. Just look at that limited edition Macbook.&amp;quot;}" class="attachment attachment--preview attachment--png"&gt;&lt;a href="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540276490-img7.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540276490-img7.png" width="800" height="409"&gt;&lt;figcaption class="attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited"&gt;The old landing page. Just look at that limited edition Macbook.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I was really pissed off at the time and I thought all the sites on Betalist look like templates because pretty much all of them &lt;em&gt;do use templates&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Anyway I just left it for a bit and decided to try and list again at a later time. Finally got around to redesigning the landing page in the new year and added a bunch of details and more information about what the site and product actually is.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;And once I re-designed the page I realised why they rejected my site the first time around.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;figure data-trix-attachment="{&amp;quot;contentType&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;image/png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filename&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;img8.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filesize&amp;quot;:288661,&amp;quot;height&amp;quot;:761,&amp;quot;href&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540299038-img8.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;url&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540299038-img8.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;width&amp;quot;:1200}" data-trix-content-type="image/png" data-trix-attributes="{&amp;quot;caption&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;The new homepage (buh-bye generic computer man stock photo)&amp;quot;}" class="attachment attachment--preview attachment--png"&gt;&lt;a href="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540299038-img8.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540299038-img8.png" width="1200" height="761"&gt;&lt;figcaption class="attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited"&gt;The new homepage (buh-bye generic computer man stock photo)&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;The &lt;a href="http://learnetto.com/"&gt;new homepage&lt;/a&gt; looks better and gives the visitor a lot more information about what the product is. It gives them much more of an incentive to actually sign up.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So I submitted the page again and, guess what, it got accepted almost immediately.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;Oh one more design tip —&amp;nbsp; &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5AxwaszFbDw"&gt;Make the logo bigger&lt;/a&gt;!&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2. Do what the Betalist team recommends&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;After the feature went live, Betalist emailed me a helpful guide on how to get the best out of the listing. They are very simple and obvious things, so you may skip them thinking it’s not worth it. But they were definitely helpful in getting a few more signups for us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3. Share the Betalist page on social media&lt;/strong&gt; — Twitter, Facebook, Snapchat, Jaiku, or whatever else you’re on. Also ask, &lt;em&gt;nay beg&lt;/em&gt;, your friends to do the same.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;figure data-trix-attachment="{&amp;quot;contentType&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;image/png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filename&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;img9.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filesize&amp;quot;:102259,&amp;quot;height&amp;quot;:534,&amp;quot;href&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540337596-img9.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;url&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540337596-img9.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;width&amp;quot;:532}" data-trix-content-type="image/png" data-trix-attributes="{&amp;quot;caption&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;That's me tweetin' - you should follow me @hrishio&amp;quot;}" class="attachment attachment--preview attachment--png"&gt;&lt;a href="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540337596-img9.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540337596-img9.png" width="532" height="534"&gt;&lt;figcaption class="attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited"&gt;That's me tweetin' - you should follow me @hrishio&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;figure data-trix-attachment="{&amp;quot;contentType&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;image/png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filename&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;img10.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filesize&amp;quot;:34465,&amp;quot;height&amp;quot;:155,&amp;quot;href&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540348570-img10.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;url&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540348570-img10.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;width&amp;quot;:526}" data-trix-content-type="image/png" data-trix-attributes="{&amp;quot;caption&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Move over, baby pictures, my startup needs some attention!&amp;quot;}" class="attachment attachment--preview attachment--png"&gt;&lt;a href="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540348570-img10.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540348570-img10.png" width="526" height="155"&gt;&lt;figcaption class="attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited"&gt;Move over, baby pictures, my startup needs some attention!&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4. Write a &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://betalist.com/startups/learnetto#comment-636"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;comment on the Betalist page&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; as per &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://twitter.com/marckohlbrugge"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Marc’s&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; suggestion.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Although my comment didn’t generate any discussion, it provides some more background about Learnetto to anyone visiting that page.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;All of these efforts combined led us to being featured in the Trending section on the Betalist homepage and the Education section too.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;figure data-trix-attachment="{&amp;quot;contentType&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;image/png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filename&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;img12.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filesize&amp;quot;:214034,&amp;quot;height&amp;quot;:677,&amp;quot;href&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540396004-img12.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;url&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540396004-img12.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;width&amp;quot;:1173}" data-trix-content-type="image/png" data-trix-attributes="{&amp;quot;caption&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;We got featured on the Betalist homepage in the Trending section!&amp;quot;}" class="attachment attachment--preview attachment--png"&gt;&lt;a href="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540396004-img12.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540396004-img12.png" width="1173" height="677"&gt;&lt;figcaption class="attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited"&gt;We got featured on the Betalist homepage in the Trending section!&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;figure data-trix-attachment="{&amp;quot;contentType&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;image/png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filename&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;img11.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filesize&amp;quot;:454845,&amp;quot;height&amp;quot;:738,&amp;quot;href&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540406082-img11.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;url&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540406082-img11.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;width&amp;quot;:1172}" data-trix-content-type="image/png" data-trix-attributes="{&amp;quot;caption&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;We also got featured in the Betalist Education section!&amp;quot;}" class="attachment attachment--preview attachment--png"&gt;&lt;a href="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540406082-img11.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540406082-img11.png" width="1172" height="738"&gt;&lt;figcaption class="attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited"&gt;We also got featured in the Betalist Education section!&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5. Show a &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://learnetto.com/thanks"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;“Thank you” page&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; after signing up and ask for referrals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Our thank you page is &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/search?f=tweets&amp;amp;vertical=default&amp;amp;q=%22Looking%20forward%20to%20some%20awesome%20courses%20on%20%40lrntto%22&amp;amp;src=typd"&gt;getting us a few tweets&lt;/a&gt; every day.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;figure data-trix-attachment="{&amp;quot;contentType&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;image/png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filename&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;img13.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filesize&amp;quot;:245777,&amp;quot;height&amp;quot;:479,&amp;quot;href&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540462275-img13.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;url&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540462275-img13.png&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;width&amp;quot;:1066}" data-trix-content-type="image/png" data-trix-attributes="{&amp;quot;caption&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Pre-fill some text they can tweet but don’t force them to use it. Be gentle.&amp;quot;}" class="attachment attachment--preview attachment--png"&gt;&lt;a href="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540462275-img13.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540462275-img13.png" width="1066" height="479"&gt;&lt;figcaption class="attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited"&gt;Pre-fill some text they can tweet but don’t force them to use it. Be gentle.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;6. Engage(TM) with signups&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;You know what I want when I wake up in the morning? I want brands to engage with me.&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;div&gt;No, but seriously, when people sign up for your beta, it means they are interested in your product and want to know more and try it out. So don’t go silent on them for months and then suddenly drop a “we’ve launched, gimme your money” email on them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I emailed our list with a super simple 1-question survey asking them which of our upcoming courses they were most interested in. A lot of people responded and it led to some useful conversations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;The other thing you can do is to make people feel special — there are so many products out there. If people are signing up for yours, give them some kind of exclusive benefit.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;7. Be ready to get listed on other similar directories like &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.betabound.com/learnetto-beta-notification/"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Betabound&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.launchingnext.com/s/learnetto/16707/"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Launching Next&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;, etc.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Once you’re on Betalist, you’ll start getting contacted by other directories. It’s best to be prepared with your logos, screenshots, tagline, short description, long description, founder bios, etc.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;8. Finally, be patient. The signups keep coming.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I was a tiny bit disappointed when I realised we didn’t even get 100 new signups on the first day. But my disappointment was short-lived because the signups kept coming the day after and the day after. The one-time spike is great but the best thing is the raised baseline of daily traffic and signups.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you enjoyed that, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://learnetto.com/"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;sign up to our mailing list&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; to get more in-depth stories about building our startup. Oh and lots of freebies and discounts on awesome courses!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;figure data-trix-attachment="{&amp;quot;contentType&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;image/gif&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filename&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;img14.gif&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;filesize&amp;quot;:370309,&amp;quot;height&amp;quot;:366,&amp;quot;href&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540478725-img14.gif&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;url&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540478725-img14.gif&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;width&amp;quot;:499}" data-trix-content-type="image/gif" data-trix-attributes="{&amp;quot;caption&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;That’s all Folks!&amp;quot;}" class="attachment attachment--preview attachment--gif"&gt;&lt;a href="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540478725-img14.gif"&gt;&lt;img src="https://assets.learnetto.com/blog/2016-02-15/1455540478725-img14.gif" width="499" height="366"&gt;&lt;figcaption class="attachment__caption attachment__caption--edited"&gt;That’s all Folks!&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Thanks to the Betalist team, especially &lt;a href="https://medium.com/u/b773a4c30c66"&gt;Marc Köhlbrugge&lt;/a&gt;, for making a great launch platform for startups and Rabia (&lt;a href="https://medium.com/u/c5b91a806c49"&gt;RPISH&lt;/a&gt;) for excellent customer support!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Also, thanks to all these lovely people for sharing their launch stories. It helped me write mine! — &lt;a href="https://medium.com/u/c04674b72608"&gt;dumpstr.io&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://medium.com/u/b7ebf7112bcc"&gt;Olivier Alcouffe&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://medium.com/u/9e7cc7ae807b"&gt;Marin Medak&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://medium.com/u/edabb1969948"&gt;Kuoll&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://medium.com/u/5f0988ea2f85"&gt;Jake Peters&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://medium.com/u/277a83f8baf3"&gt;Oskar Glauser&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="http://twitter.com/_sergeh"&gt;@_serge&lt;/a&gt;h, &lt;a href="https://medium.com/u/e2f2e1223230"&gt;Alexander Weidauer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://medium.com/u/afc0fd9cd757"&gt;Aditya Gopal Ganguly&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="http://twitter.com/gym_selfie"&gt;@gym_selfi&lt;/a&gt;e and&lt;a href="https://medium.com/u/30465bf6f860"&gt;Tim Perry&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
